  1. GPD and life expectancy:
gapminder %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=gdpPercap, y=lifeExp))+
  geom_point(size = 0.2)+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = TRUE)+
  labs(title = "Life Expectancy and GDP",
       x = "GDP",
       y = "Life expectancy")

  1. Rescaling the graph:
gapminder %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=gdpPercap, y=lifeExp))+
  geom_point(size = 0.4)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = TRUE)+
  labs(title = "Life Expectancy and GDP",
       x = "GDP",
       y = "Life expectancy")

  1. Faceting the graph:
gapminder %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=gdpPercap, y=lifeExp))+
  geom_point(size=0.3)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  facet_wrap(~year)+
  labs(title = "Life Expectance and GDP")

  1. Filter the graph:
gapminder %>%
  filter(year==1952 | year==2007) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=gdpPercap, y=lifeExp))+
  geom_point(size=0.3)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  facet_wrap(~year)+
  labs(title = "Life Expectance and GDP")

6.More Filtering:

gapminder %>%
  filter(year==1952 | year==2007) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=gdpPercap, y=lifeExp, size = pop, color = continent))+
  geom_point(size=0.3)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  facet_wrap(~year)+
  labs(title = "Life Expectance and GDP, Refined")+
  scale_size(range = c(0.1, 10))

  1. Applying a theme to the plot:

8.Population barlplot:

gapminder %>%
  filter(year==2007 & continent=="Asia") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(country, pop), y=pop))+
  geom_col(fill="green", alpha=0.6)+
  coord_flip()+
  labs(title = "Population, Asia",
       x = "Population",
       y = "Country")

9.Population change:

gapminder %>%
  filter(country=="China") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=factor(year), y=pop))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity")+
  labs(title = "Population Growth", x = "Year", y = "Population")+
  coord_flip()

  1. Population comparison:
gapminder %>%
  filter(country=="India" | country=="China") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=factor(year), y=pop, fill=country))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position="dodge")+
  labs(title = "Population Growth, compared",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Pop")
